Java Full Stack 

1. What is Programming Language?
->A programming language is a formal language used to write instructions that a computer can understand and execute to perform tasks.

2. What is Assembler?
->An assembler is a system program that converts assembly language code into machine language.

3. What is MicroProcessor?
->A microprocessor is the central processing unit (CPU) on a single chip that performs arithmetic, logic, and control operations of a computer.

4. What is Compiler?
A compiler is a software that translates an entire high-level programming language program into machine code before execution.

Evolution of Language:
a.fortrain - 1957
b.cobol    - 1959
c.BCPL     - 1962
4.B        - 1969
5.C        - 1972
