7.oak/Java - 1995

Memory Devices 
HDD - Hard Disk Drive
RAM - Random Access Memory

Flow of c program
.c -> c compiler -> .obj  -> linking loader -> .exe -> microprocessor -> output

Debugging in c
.c -> interpreter -> obj line -> linking loader -> .exe -> microprocessor -> output
                                                               ^
                                                               |
                                                               operating system

Compiler vs Interpreter
Compiler: Translates the entire program into machine code at once before execution.
Interpreter: Translates and executes the program line by line at runtime.


5. Why c and c++ is platform dependent?
-> C and C++ are considered platform dependent because they are compiled into machine code specific to the operating system and hardware architecture.
Once compiled, the generated executable works only on that particular platform (e.g., Windows, Linux, x86, ARM) unless recompiled for another platform.


